Baya ga waɗannan abubuwa uku na kwayar cutar da aka ambata a sama, wani muhimmin abu mai mahimmanci don watsawa tsakanin jinsuna shine hulɗar kwayar cutar tare da mai karɓar mai ɗaukar hoto.
Wannan labarin ya ba da misali na yau da kullun wanda kuma ya nuna hujja game da zaɓin zaɓi mai kyau a cikin abubuwan watsawa tsakanin nau'ikan halittu, sake haɗuwa da SARS-CoV.
Bisa ga nazarin kwatancen tsakanin SARS-CoV na mutum da kuma na civet, an yi imanin cewa SARS-CoV yana da saurin daidaitawa a cikin masu ɗaukar hoto daban-daban, musamman game da maye gurbi a cikin RSD na furotin S.
Gabaɗaya, ƙwayar cuta ta S ta ƙwayar cuta ta ƙwayar cuta tana hulɗa da mai karɓar ƙwayoyin cuta, kuma amsar ƙwayar cuta ta ƙwayar cuta tana karɓar shi sosai.
RSD a cikin SARS-CoV  amino acid ne, daga 318th zuwa 510th, akan S1 yanki wanda don shigar da kwayar cutar cikin tantanin halitta yana haɗuwa da enzyme mai canza angiotensin 2 na mutum (APF2), da kuma masu karɓar sa.
SARS-CoV RSD yana iya gane masu karɓar APF2 na dabbobi daban-daban, gami da bera, civet, linzamin kwamfuta da kare, yana ba da damar watsa kwayar cutar tsakanin nau'ikan.
A zahiri, an gano ragowar amino acid guda 6 ne kawai a cikin RSD waɗanda suka bambanta da nau'ikan kwayar cutar ɗan adam da civet, tare da 4 daga cikinsu suna cikin ƙwayar haɗin mai karɓa don hulɗa tare da mai karɓar APF2.
SARS-CoV civet yana da maye gurbi K479N da S487T a cikin RCD, wanda zai iya haɓaka alaƙar haɗin gwiwar furotin mai ƙwanƙwasa tare da mai karɓar APF2 na ɗan adam.
Watau, waɗannan amino acid biyu da aka maye gurbin su suna da muhimmanci sosai wajen sa kwayar cutar ta zama ta mutum.
Ya kamata a lura cewa SARS-CoV-2 yana da irin wannan mai karɓar ƙwayoyin cuta kamar SARS-CoV.
Bambanci na 30% tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da SARS-CoV a cikin ɓangaren S1 na furotin S yana haifar da cewa alaƙar S protein zuwa APF2 na mutum na iya canzawa.
A gaskiya, binciken da aka yi da na'urar daukar hotan lantarki ya nuna cewa wannan dangantaka ta fi ta mutum 10 zuwa 20 fiye da ta APF2 da kuma SARS-CoV S protein.
Hakanan zai zama mai ban sha'awa don gano ko ana buƙatar wasu masu karɓar kwayar cutar don watsa SARS-CoV-2.
Abin mamaki, HCoV-NL63 kuma yana ɗaure da APF2, amma da wani ɓangaren S protein.
Akwai wasu masu karɓar HCoV da yawa, kamar aminopeptidease N don HCoV-229E da 9-O-acetylsilic acid don HCoV-OC43.
Hakanan suna iya zama masu alhakin nasarar daidaita waɗannan coronaviruses a cikin mutane bayan watsawa tsakanin nau'ikan daga dabbobi masu ɗaukar su.
Baya ga masu karɓar ƙwayoyin halitta, sakamakon watsa HCoV tsakanin jinsuna yana sarrafawa ta wasu abubuwan dogaro da iyakance mai ɗaukar hoto.
Bambancin waɗannan furotin masu ɗaukar hoto tsakanin mutane da masu ɗaukar hoto na HCoVs na halitta kamar barbashi, raƙuma masu ƙwanƙwasawa da rodents na iya zama shinge don watsawa tsakanin jinsuna.
Don samun nasarar yaduwar HCoVs tsakanin jinsuna, dole ne su mamaye abubuwan dogaro da kuma sarrafa abubuwan ƙuntatawa na masu ɗaukar su.
A wannan yanayin, ƙwayoyin ƙwayoyin halitta a cikin wannan muhimmin yanki na hulɗa tsakanin kwayar cuta da mai ɗaukar hoto har yanzu suna buƙatar ƙayyadewa da rarrabuwa.
Za a iya samun sakamako mai kyau ta hanyar bincika kwayoyin halittar SARS-CoV-2 ta hanyar amfani da sabuwar fasahar CRISPR.
