Bambancin kwayar cutar coronavirus na bera yana ba da dama ga sababbin HCoVs.
A wannan ma'anar, ƙwayoyin cuta na corona na ƙwari suna aiki a matsayin tarin kwayoyin halitta don HCoV.
Bugu da ƙari, sauye-sauye da sauye-sauyen kwayoyin halitta suna motsa juyin HCoV kuma suna aiki a matsayin matakai biyu masu muhimmanci a cikin wannan tsari.
Alal misali, samun ko kuma rasa sababbin kwayoyin halittar da ke ƙunshe da furotin yana iya canja yanayin ƙwayoyin cuta.
Daga cikin furotin na SARS-CoV, ORF8 yana da mahimmanci don daidaitawa ga mutane, saboda an ware ƙwayoyin cuta na bera, waɗanda ke da alaƙa da SARS-CoV, amma an gano cewa suna ɓoye furotin masu bambancin ORF8.
An gano raguwar kwayoyin halittar 29-nucleotide a cikin nau'ikan da aka ware a farkon annobar ɗan adam, wanda ya dace da coronavirus SARS-CoV.
Wannan canjin ya raba ORF8 zuwa ORF8a da ORF8b, kuma an ɗauka cewa canjin canji ne wanda ke saurin sauya masu ɗauke da shi.
Bugu da ƙari, SARS-CoV yana da tarihin yiwuwar sake haɗuwa tare da layin alpha da gamma coronaviruses, inda aka gano ƙananan ƙananan wuraren haɗuwa a cikin RNA-da ke da alaƙa da RNA polymerase.
An kuma gano wuraren sake haɗuwa a cikin furotin mara tsari na nsp9, yawancin nsp10, da kuma sassan nsp14.
